@node config
 The Config program
 ==================

  There are two versions of the config program, one with GUI (Graphical User
  Interface), and one STDIO (STandarD Input Output (Like in a shell window))
  There is no difference between them, except for the fact that the GUI
  version looks nicer ;).

  When you start the Config program, you will be presented with these
  buttons:

  @{"System  Paths" Link config_syspath}
  @{" Multi  Line " Link config_mline}
  @{"Message  Base" Link config_mbase}
  @{"  File Base  " Link config_fbase}
  @{"Access Levels" Link config_axx}
  @{"Miscellaneous" Link config_misc}
  @{"  XPR Setup  " Link config_xpr}
  @{" Macro  Keys " Link config_macro}

  Click @{"here" Link configstdio} for info about the Config-STDIO.

@endnode

@node config_syspath
 System paths
 ============

  Message Directory:
    Where all the message base files should be kept.

  Textfile Directory:
    Where Reccoon will look for all textfiles.
    (The ones ending in .TXT or .GR<nr>)

  Menufile Directory:
    Where Reccoon will look for the menu pages, and the two main FPL scripts:
        Logon.FPL (Runned at logon and replaces builtin standards)
        RcnMenus.FPL (Runned instead of MenuPage 1)

  WaitingMail Directory:
    Where Reccoon will store all Waiting mail pointers.

  Outbound Directory:
    Where all outgoing fidomail will be stored.

  Inbound Directory:
    This is where ReccProc will search for incoming mail.

  Filedata Directory:
    Where all FileBase related files will be stored.

  Tmp Upload Directory:
    A directory containing a Tmp<node> for each line.
    This is where ALL uploads will be, before they get uploaded in the bbs.
@endnode

@node config_mline
 Multi Line
 ==========

  When you press this, you get presented with a new window with all the
  nodes in the system. If you click on an existing node, you'll be presented
  with it's settings. If you press "Create New Node", it will ask you what
  line number the new node should have. When created, select the new node to
  get to the settings window.

 Settings
 ========



@node support
